{
  "texts": [
    "The concept is that knowledge within the language model can be retrieved through direct text generation [17].",
    "For example, the Selfmem framework [7] ingeniously employs a generator to repeatedly produce synthesized texts, forming an unlimited memory pool for future use.",
    "This model uniquely uses its own generated outputs as self-memory to aid subsequent generation, showcasing an innovative approach where text generation helps fabricate new memory references.",
    "Another notable method is RECITE [39], which is designed to enable LLMs to produce relevant information without resorting to external data sources.",
    "It first prompts the LLM to recite relevant passages based on its internal knowledge."
  ]
}